# PowerShell Environment

All terminal commands MUST use PowerShell syntax. NEVER use bash syntax.

## Core Rules

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| Multiline strings | MUST use `@'...'@` or `-F file` |
| Command chaining | MUST use `;` not `&&` or `\|\|` |
| Variables | MUST use `$env:VAR` not `export VAR` |
| Heredocs | NEVER use `<<EOF` (bash only) |

## Command Patterns

| Bash | PowerShell |
|------|------------|
| `cmd1 && cmd2` | `cmd1; if ($?) { cmd2 }` or separate commands |
| `export VAR="val"` | `$env:VAR = "val"` |
| `cat file \| grep x` | `rg x file` (use cross-platform tools) |

## Prefer Cross-Platform Tools

Use Cursor tools over shell commands: Read, StrReplace, Grep, Glob instead of `cat`, `sed`, `grep`, `find`.
